{
  "stem": "3820.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I-- the Russians liberated that part of Ukrainia [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the-- in the fall of-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] no, the spring of '44 or the-- somewhere in there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And so that when he came, it was very shortly after that, maybe a couple of months.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And at first, I didn't want to go with him, because when my other uncle died, they had said that six partisans died, and two of them were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the last that I had known, my uncle Sana and my uncle Chaim were together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So it was hard for me to accept that he was really there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But he stayed a couple of days on the farm with me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then the lady went with us back to Kiev, Anna.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And she left me there with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we lived in Kiev with a couple, Grisha and-- and his wife, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] who were also partisans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "My uncle had been wounded and heroically decorated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But when the part of Poland where we come from, which is near Lublin, was liberated by the Russians, my uncle asked permission to go to Lublin to see if we had any survivors there.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] It's-- it's hard to remember everything and I--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I-- yes, I do.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- my grandfather announced that he was going back for the high holiday services.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everyone started arguing with him, that we had gotten out of the ghetto and why was he doing this?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said that it was important for him to be there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He-- he had never in his whole life missed a Kol Nidrei service, and he didn't intend to do it this time.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
